Class Repository

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.pulumi.resources.Resource

        • com.pulumi.dbtcloud.Repository
  • public class Repository
extends com.pulumi.resources.CustomResource
    *Note*: Some upstream resources can be slow to create, so if creating a project at the same time as the repository, it's recommended to use the `depends_on` meta argument. In order to find the `github_installation_id`, you can log in to dbt Cloud, replace `<dbt_cloud_url>` by your dbt Cloud URL and run the following commands in the Google Chrome console: Alternatively, you can go to the page `https://<dbt_cloud_url>/api/v2/integrations/github/installations/` and read the value of `id` or use the `http` provider to retrieve it automatically like in the example below. ## Example Usage ## Import Import using a project ID and repository ID found in the URL or via the API. ```sh $ pulumi import dbtcloud:index/repository:Repository test_repository "project_id:repository_id" ``` ```sh $ pulumi import dbtcloud:index/repository:Repository test_repository 12345:6789 ```

        The Azure Dev Ops project ID. It can be retrieved via the Azure API or using the data source `dbtcloud.getAzureDevOpsProject` and the project name - (for ADO native integration only)

      • azureActiveDirectoryRepositoryId

        public com.pulumi.core.Output<java.util.Optional<java.lang.String>> azureActiveDirectoryRepositoryId()
        Returns:
        The Azure Dev Ops repository ID. It can be retrieved via the Azure API or using the data source `dbtcloud.getAzureDevOpsRepository` along with the ADO Project ID and the repository name - (for ADO native integration only)

      • azureBypassWebhookRegistrationFailure

        public com.pulumi.core.Output<java.util.Optional<java.lang.Boolean>> azureBypassWebhookRegistrationFailure()
        Returns:
        If set to False (the default), the connection will fail if the service user doesn't have access to set webhooks (required for auto-triggering CI jobs). If set to True, the connection will be successful but no automated CI job will be triggered - (for ADO native integration only)

        public com.pulumi.core.Output<java.util.Optional<java.lang.String>> gitCloneStrategy()

        Git clone strategy for the repository. Can be `deploy_key` (default) for cloning via SSH Deploy Key, `github_app` for GitHub native integration, `deploy_token` for the GitLab native integration and `azure_active_directory_app` for ADO native integration
